{"type":"text","timestamp":1782887165503,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"id":"prt_f1c5b0005001lqOtaC6SeO6cbW","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","type":"text","text":"The key contrast is now concrete: `deep.md` uses a registry table plus consistency gates, while `orchestrate.md` still asks a general primary agent to decompose and derive the route before delegation. Next I’m checking the command YAML and plugin hook surfaces to ground the proposed benchmark and enforcement options.","time":{"start":1782887153669,"end":1782887165501},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2f1a8a8819198abd66d24c1cab7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165567,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QNWlzxnGNWidKEmP09e7pkry","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\n8: \n9: Thin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: > **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n18: \n19: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n20: >\n21: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n22: >\n23: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n24: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n25: > 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n26: >    - `research_topic`\n27: >    - `spec_folder`\n28: >    - `execution_mode`\n29: >    - `maxIterations`\n30: >    - `convergenceThreshold`\n31: >    - `dry_run` (default false unless `--dry-run` is present)\n32: > 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n33: >    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n34: >    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n35: > 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n36: >\n37: > This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n38: \n39: ### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n40: \n41: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n42: \n43: ```\n44: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n45: \n46: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n47: │\n48: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n49: │   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-research loop (YAML workflow execution)\n50: │   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n51: │   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n52: │\n53: ├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n54: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n55: │\n56: └─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n57:     │\n58:     ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n59:     │\n60:     ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n61:     │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n62:     │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n63:     │   │                                                            │\n64:     │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n65:     │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n66:     │   │                                                            │\n67:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n68:     │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n69:     │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n70:     │\n71:     └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n72: ```\n73: \n74: **Phase Output:**\n75: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n76: \n77: ### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n78: \n79: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n80: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n81: - **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n82: - **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n83:   - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n84:   - `dry_run` is normalized to `true` or `false`; absence means `false`\n85: \n86: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n87: \n88: > **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`) and keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n89: \n90: > **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n91: > `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n92: > Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n93: > Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator; the current strict path is designed for fast packet checks and was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n98: \n99: | Purpose | Asset |\n100: |---------|-------|\n101: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n102: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n103: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n104: \n105: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## 3. MODE ROUTING\n110: \n111: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n112: 2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--dry-run`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n113: 3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n114: 4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n115: 5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n116: 6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n117: 7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n118: 8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n119: \n120: ### Dry-Run Flag\n121: \n122: `--dry-run` is a first-class flag on the confirm flow, not a third execution mode. It still performs real setup resolution, artifact-root resolution, focus selection, prompt rendering, and convergence reads when those steps can run without side effects.\n123: \n124: When `dry_run=true`, the confirm YAML emits `dry_run_halt` JSONL preview lines to terminal output instead of appending to the live state log, and halts before executor dispatch, persistent state mutation, reducer refresh, or child-lineage spawn. A fresh packet will stop at the first persistent state boundary; an existing packet can read current state and convergence signals, render the next prompt for preview, then stop before dispatch.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n129: \n130: | Mode | Workflow |\n131: |------|----------|\n132: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n133: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n138: \n139: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n140: \n141: - Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n142: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n143: - Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n144: - Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n145: - Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n150: \n151: The selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n152: \n153: For code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.\n\n(End of file - total 153 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the @general verification gate before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-context loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │ \n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","text":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n> 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n> 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n>    - `research_topic`\n>    - `spec_folder`\n>    - `execution_mode`\n>    - `maxIterations`\n>    - `convergenceThreshold`\n>    - `dry_run` (default false unless `--dry-run` is present)\n> 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n>    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n> 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n>\n> This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-research loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n  - `dry_run` is normalized to `true` or `false`; absence means `false`\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n\n> **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`) and keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n\n> **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n> `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n> Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n> Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator; the current strict path is designed for fast packet checks and was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--dry-run`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n\n### Dry-Run Flag\n\n`--dry-run` is a first-class flag on the confirm flow, not a third execution mode. It still performs real setup resolution, artifact-root resolution, focus selection, prompt rendering, and convergence reads when those steps can run without side effects.\n\nWhen `dry_run=true`, the confirm YAML emits `dry_run_halt` JSONL preview lines to terminal output instead of appending to the live state log, and halts before executor dispatch, persistent state mutation, reducer refresh, or child-lineage spawn. A fresh packet will stop at the first persistent state boundary; an existing packet can read current state and convergence signals, render the next prompt for preview, then stop before dispatch.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n- Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n- Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":153,"totalLines":153,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/research.md","time":{"start":1782887165561,"end":1782887165565}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd738c8191a2069ca36712771c"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2e3e001RmOy8V6v431i08","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165610,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_IbYU6IWsZUUvfbW0SQBgdR1o","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":800,"limit":210},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n800:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n801:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n802:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n803:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n804:                 halt with exit code 2\n805:         note: |\n806:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n807:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n808:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n809:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n810: \n811:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n812:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n813:         resolve_executor:\n814:           source: \"config.executor\"\n815:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n816:         pre_dispatch:\n817:           generate_summary: |\n818:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n819:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n820:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n821:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n822:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n823:             {memory_context_prompt_line}\n824:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n825:           render_prompt_pack:\n826:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n827:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n828:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n829:             variables:\n830:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n831:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n832:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n833:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n834:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n835:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n836:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n837:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n838:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n839:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n840:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n841:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n842:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n843:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n844:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n845:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n846:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n847:           args:\n848:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n849:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n850:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n851:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n852:         if_native:\n853:           dispatch:\n854:             agent: deep-research\n855:             model: opus\n856:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n857:           wait_for_completion: true\n858:         if_cli_claude_code:\n859:           command: |\n860:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n861:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n862: \n863:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n864:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n865: \n866:             const executor = {\n867:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n868:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n869:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n870:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n871:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n872:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n873:             };\n874:             const args = [\n875:               '-p',\n876:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n877:               '--model',\n878:               executor.model,\n879:               '--permission-mode',\n880:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n881:               '--output-format',\n882:               'text',\n883:             ];\n884:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n885:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n886:             }\n887: \n888:             process.exit(\n889:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n890:                 command: 'claude',\n891:                 args,\n892:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n893:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n894:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n895:                 executor,\n896:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n897:               }),\n898:             );\n899:             EOF\n900:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n901:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n902:           wait_for_completion: true\n903:           notes:\n904:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n905:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n906:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n907:         record_executor_audit:\n908:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n909:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n910:           field: \"executor\"\n911:           value:\n912:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n913:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n914:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n915:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n916:         if_cli_opencode:\n917:           command: |\n918:             opencode run \\\n919:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n920:               --format json \\\n921:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n922:               --pure \\\n923:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n924:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n925:               \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n926:               </dev/null\n927:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n928:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n929:           wait_for_completion: true\n930:           render_hint:\n931:             optional_variant_flag: |\n932:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n933:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n934:           notes:\n935:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n936:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n937:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n938:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n939:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n940:         post_dispatch_validate:\n941:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n942:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n943:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n944:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n945:           route_proof:\n946:             mode: research\n947:             target_agent: deep-research\n948:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n949:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n950:           optional_jsonl_fields:\n951:             logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n952:             logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n953:             logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n954:             skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n955:             slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n956:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n957:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n958:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n959:           on_failure:\n960:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n961:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n962:           failure_reasons_reference:\n963:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n964:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n965:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n966:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n967:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n968:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n969:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n970:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n971:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n972:             - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n973:             - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n974:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n975:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n976: \n977:       step_run_now_restore_check:\n978:         action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n979:         command: |\n980:           node <<'EOF'\n981:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n982: \n983:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n984:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n985:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n986:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n987:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n988:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n989: \n990:           function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n991:             if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n992:             const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n993:             for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n994:               const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n995:               if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n996:               if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n997:               if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n998:             }\n999:             return false;\n1000:           }\n1001: \n1002:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n1003:             appendFileSync(\n1004:               stateLogPath,\n1005:               `${JSON.stringify({\n1006:                 type: \"event\",\n1007:                 event: \"run_now_restored\",\n1008:                 mode: \"research\",\n1009:                 run,\n\n(Showing lines 800-1009 of 1517. Use offset=1010 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            {memory_context_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: research\n            target_agent: deep-research\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n          optional_jsonl_fields:\n            logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n            logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n            logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n            skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n            slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n            if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n            const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n            for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n              const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n              if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n            }\n            return false;\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                event: \"run_now_restored\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,","lineStart":800,"lineEnd":1009,"totalLines":1517,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782887165605,"end":1782887165609}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd73a88191b05871727c78b1f9"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2e7c001vROcTZs4Quldc4","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165682,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6gMgurz1M36pSF6gy3exXDgv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":760,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n760:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n761:         pre_dispatch:\n762:           generate_summary: |\n763:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n764:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n765:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n766:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n767:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n768:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n769:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n770:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n771:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n772:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n773:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n774:           render_prompt_pack:\n775:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n776:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n777:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n778:             variables:\n779:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n780:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n781:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n782:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n783:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n784:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n785:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n786:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n787:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n788:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n789:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n790:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n791:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n792:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n793:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n794:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n795:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n796:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n797:           args:\n798:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n799:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n800:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n801:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n802:         if_native:\n803:           dispatch:\n804:             agent: deep-review\n805:             model: opus\n806:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n807:           wait_for_completion: true\n808:         if_cli_copilot:\n809:           command: |\n810:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n811:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n812:             import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n813: \n814:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n815: \n816:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n817:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n818: \n819:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n820:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n821:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n822:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n823:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n824:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n825:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n826:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n827:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n828: \n829:             const baseArgs = [\n830:               '-p',\n831:               prompt,\n832:               '--model',\n833:               '{config.executor.model}',\n834:               '--allow-all-tools',\n835:               '--no-ask-user',\n836:             ];\n837: \n838:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n839:               promptPath,\n840:               prompt,\n841:               targetAuthority,\n842:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n843:             });\n844: \n845:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n846:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n847:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n848:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n849:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n850:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n851:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n852:             }\n853: \n854:             const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n855:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n856:               stdio: 'inherit',\n857:               timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n858:             });\n859:             process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n860:             EOF\n861:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n862:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n863:           wait_for_completion: true\n864:           notes:\n865:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n866:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n867:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n868:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n869:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n870:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n871:         if_cli_claude_code:\n872:           command: |\n873:             if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n874:             claude \\\n875:               -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n876:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n877:               --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n878:               --output-format text \\\n879:               {optional_effort_flag}\n880:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n881:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n882:           wait_for_completion: true\n883:           render_hint:\n884:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n885:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n886:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n887:             optional_effort_flag: |\n888:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n889:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n890:           notes:\n891:             - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n892:             - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n893:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n894:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n895:         if_cli_opencode:\n896:           command: |\n897:             opencode run \\\n898:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n899:               --format json \\\n900:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n901:               --pure \\\n902:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n903:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n904:               \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n905:               </dev/null\n906:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n907:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n908:           wait_for_completion: true\n909:           render_hint:\n910:             optional_variant_flag: |\n911:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n912:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n913:           notes:\n914:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n915:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n916:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n917:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n918:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n919:         post_dispatch_validate:\n920:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n921:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n922:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n923:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n924:           route_proof:\n925:             mode: review\n926:             target_agent: deep-review\n927:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n928:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n929:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n930:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n931:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n932:           failure_reasons:\n933:             - iteration_file_missing\n934:             - iteration_file_empty\n935:             - jsonl_not_appended\n936:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n937:             - jsonl_parse_error\n938:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n939:             - delta_file_missing\n\n(Showing lines 760-939 of 1444. Use offset=940 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              stdio: 'inherit',\n              timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n            });\n            process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n            claude \\\n              -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n              --output-format text \\\n              {optional_effort_flag}\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n            optional_effort_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n            - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: review\n            target_agent: deep-review\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing","lineStart":760,"lineEnd":939,"totalLines":1444,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782887165677,"end":1782887165681}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd73b481919394c96449d1b457"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2eb4001EnYOBp5RYPfhFG","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165782,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_39VWW8XKBhG4zCslpEE43AfJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","offset":360,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n360:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n361:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n362:         if_exists:\n363:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n364:           message: \"Context loop paused. Delete context/.deep-context-pause to resume.\"\n365:           halt: true\n366:         if_not_exists:\n367:           proceed: true\n368: \n369:       # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n370:       # THE PARALLEL HETEROGENEOUS SWEEP\n371:       # All seats analyze the SAME current_focus. native batch ‖ CLI pool\n372:       # start TOGETHER and barrier-join. Seats are READ-ONLY; they write\n373:       # only their own seats/iter-NNN/{label}.json. The host merges after.\n374:       # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n375:       step_render_seat_prompts:\n376:         action: \"Render ONE prompt per seat for the SHARED current focus, carrying the full lineage contract\"\n377:         ensure_dirs: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration} {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\"\n378:         for_each: \"seat in config.fanout.executors\"\n379:         contract_per_seat: |\n380:           Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true\n381: \n382:           Every seat prompt MUST carry the four-part lineage contract (a seat told only \"analyze\"\n383:           returns generic noise):\n384:             1. gather-subject: \"{scope}\"\n385:             2. scope/slice: the SHARED current_focus (this iteration's SLICE set) — identical for ALL seats\n386:             3. known-context: prior_context_summary + already-confirmed reuse candidates (avoid re-finding)\n387:             4. output schema: the structured-finding JSON the host expects (see seat_output_schema below)\n388:         prompt_framing:\n389:           rule: \"Apply each seat's promptFramework via sk-prompt-models (MiMo→COSTAR, MiniMax/DeepSeek→TIDD-EC). Native seats use no framework wrapper.\"\n390:           loader: \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\"\n391:         seat_output_schema: |\n392:           { \"findings\": [ { \"unit_id\": \"sha256(path:symbol:kind)\", \"path\": \"...\", \"symbol\": \"...\",\n393:             \"kind\": \"reuse_candidate|integration_point|convention|dependency|gap\",\n394:             \"signature\": \"...\", \"reuse\": \"extend|compose|wrap|import\", \"evidence\": \"file:line\",\n395:             \"relevance\": 0.0, \"notes\": \"...\" } ] }\n396:         output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md\"\n397: \n398:       step_parallel_sweep:\n399:         action: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over the SHARED current focus CONCURRENTLY; barrier-join\"\n400:         note: |\n401:           This is the defining step. The native batch AND the CLI pool start TOGETHER (true\n402:           heterogeneous parallelism: 2 native + N CLI all at once) and the host waits for ALL\n403:           seats before merging. Both sub-steps below are launched WITHOUT waiting for each other.\n404:         launch_together: [step_sweep_native_batch, step_sweep_cli_pool]\n405:         barrier_join: \"Wait for BOTH step_sweep_native_batch AND step_sweep_cli_pool to settle before step_merge_findings\"\n406:         sub_steps:\n407: \n408:           step_sweep_native_batch:\n409:             description: \"Dispatch ALL native seats as a SINGLE PARALLEL BATCH (one parallel batch, NOT a sequential for_each)\"\n410:             skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n411:             dispatch_mode: parallel_batch\n412:             critical: |\n413:               NATIVE-PARALLEL REQUIREMENT: emit ALL native @deep-context Task dispatches in ONE batch\n414:               (a single set of concurrent Task calls), NOT one-at-a-time in a loop. Each native seat\n415:               gets the SAME current_focus and its own rendered prompt. Read-only analyzers.\n416:             batch:\n417:               for_each_native_seat: \"seat in native entries of config.fanout.executors\"\n418:               dispatch:\n419:                 agent: deep-context\n420:                 model: opus\n421:                 read_only: true\n422:                 context_source: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md\"\n423:                 returns: \"structured findings (seat_output_schema)\"\n424:                 host_writes: \"Host writes each seat's return to {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.json\"\n425:             wait_for_completion: true\n426: \n427:           step_sweep_cli_pool:\n428:             description: \"Dispatch ALL CLI seats as ONE-SHOT analysis seats over the SHARED focus, in parallel\"\n429:             skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n430:             dispatch_mode: one_shot_analysis_council\n431:             critical: |\n432:               ONE-SHOT-ANALYSIS REQUIREMENT (by-model shared scope): each CLI seat performs exactly ONE\n433:               read-only analysis pass over the SHARED current_focus this iteration — identical to a native\n434:               seat, just a different model lens. A CLI seat does NOT run its own loop. Use the council\n435:               parallel scaffold, NOT the autonomous-lineage runner, for the per-iteration sweep.\n436:             primary:\n437:               tool: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs#dispatchCouncilSeats\"\n438:               note: |\n439:                 Orchestrate the CLI seats from the Node host via the council scaffold:\n440:                   dispatchCouncilSeats({ roundId, seats, dispatchSeat, context })\n441:                 fans the seats out with Promise.all and aggregates per-seat results (fulfilled/rejected +\n442:                 duration). roundId = \"iter-{current_iteration}\". seats = config.fanout.executors filtered to\n443:                 kind != 'native', each carrying its rendered prompt path and the SHARED current_focus.\n444:               dispatch_seat: |\n445:                 The injected per-seat dispatch function issues a SINGLE one-shot read-only CLI analysis\n446:                 call — one `opencode run` / ` exec` / `claude -p` per seat — NOT a\n447:                 loop. Build each invocation's per-kind flag shape by reusing\n448:                 scripts/fanout-run.cjs#buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, sandbox, permission); the\n449:                 difference is the PROMPT (one-shot analysis contract below, NOT buildLoopPrompt's\n450:                 \"run phase_init/phase_main_loop/phase_synthesis\" text). The host then writes each seat's\n451:                 returned findings JSON to {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.json.\n452:               one_shot_prompt_contract: |\n453:                 Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true\n454: \n455:                 Each seat's one-shot prompt carries the four-part lineage contract from\n456:                 step_render_seat_prompts (gather-subject {scope} + SHARED current_focus + known-context +\n457:                 seat_output_schema) and instructs the seat to return ONLY the structured-finding JSON for\n458:                 this single pass. Apply the seat's promptFramework via sk-prompt-models\n459:                 (MiMo→COSTAR, MiniMax/DeepSeek→TIDD-EC). Source the prompt body from the per-seat file\n460:                 rendered at {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md.\n461:             optional_autonomous_lineage_mode:\n462:               when: \"operator opt-in only (config.fanout.cliMode == 'autonomous-lineage'); NEVER the default per-iteration path\"\n463:               tool: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\"\n464:               command: |\n465:                 node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n466:                   --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n467:                   --loop-type context \\\n468:                   --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_cli_json}' \\\n469:                   --base-artifact-dir {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\n470:               working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n471:               note: |\n472:                 fanout-run.cjs spawns AUTONOMOUS FULL-LOOP lineages (buildLoopPrompt tells each subprocess\n473:                 to run phase_init/phase_main_loop/phase_synthesis to convergence). That is the\n474:                 research/review autonomous-lineage model — it is NOT by-model shared scope and must NOT be\n475:                 used for the per-iteration parallel sweep. Reserve it for an explicit operator opt-in where\n476:                 each CLI executor should run its OWN context loop end-to-end and the host merges the\n477:                 lineage reports afterward (via scripts/fanout-merge.cjs), not per-iteration findings.\n478:             cli_contract:\n479:               - \"cli-opencode seats: dispatched with closed stdin (</dev/null) and NO top-level --agent (current opencode rejects --agent general); model id form per cli-opencode SKILL.md.\"\n\n(Showing lines 360-479 of 840. Use offset=480 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Context loop paused. Delete context/.deep-context-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      # THE PARALLEL HETEROGENEOUS SWEEP\n      # All seats analyze the SAME current_focus. native batch ‖ CLI pool\n      # start TOGETHER and barrier-join. Seats are READ-ONLY; they write\n      # only their own seats/iter-NNN/{label}.json. The host merges after.\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      step_render_seat_prompts:\n        action: \"Render ONE prompt per seat for the SHARED current focus, carrying the full lineage contract\"\n        ensure_dirs: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration} {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\"\n        for_each: \"seat in config.fanout.executors\"\n        contract_per_seat: |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Context loop paused. Delete context/.deep-context-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      # THE PARALLEL HETEROGENEOUS SWEEP\n      # All seats analyze the SAME current_focus. native batch ‖ CLI pool\n      # start TOGETHER and barrier-join. Seats are READ-ONLY; they write\n      # only their own seats/iter-NNN/{label}.json. The host merges after.\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      step_render_seat_prompts:\n        action: \"Render ONE prompt per seat for the SHARED current focus, carrying the full lineage contract\"\n        ensure_dirs: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration} {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\"\n        for_each: \"seat in config.fanout.executors\"\n        contract_per_seat: |\n          Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true\n\n          Every seat prompt MUST carry the four-part lineage contract (a seat told only \"analyze\"\n          returns generic noise):\n            1. gather-subject: \"{scope}\"\n            2. scope/slice: the SHARED current_focus (this iteration's SLICE set) — identical for ALL seats\n            3. known-context: prior_context_summary + already-confirmed reuse candidates (avoid re-finding)\n            4. output schema: the structured-finding JSON the host expects (see seat_output_schema below)\n        prompt_framing:\n          rule: \"Apply each seat's promptFramework via sk-prompt-models (MiMo→COSTAR, MiniMax/DeepSeek→TIDD-EC). Native seats use no framework wrapper.\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\"\n        seat_output_schema: |\n          { \"findings\": [ { \"unit_id\": \"sha256(path:symbol:kind)\", \"path\": \"...\", \"symbol\": \"...\",\n            \"kind\": \"reuse_candidate|integration_point|convention|dependency|gap\",\n            \"signature\": \"...\", \"reuse\": \"extend|compose|wrap|import\", \"evidence\": \"file:line\",\n            \"relevance\": 0.0, \"notes\": \"...\" } ] }\n        output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md\"\n\n      step_parallel_sweep:\n        action: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over the SHARED current focus CONCURRENTLY; barrier-join\"\n        note: |\n          This is the defining step. The native batch AND the CLI pool start TOGETHER (true\n          heterogeneous parallelism: 2 native + N CLI all at once) and the host waits for ALL\n          seats before merging. Both sub-steps below are launched WITHOUT waiting for each other.\n        launch_together: [step_sweep_native_batch, step_sweep_cli_pool]\n        barrier_join: \"Wait for BOTH step_sweep_native_batch AND step_sweep_cli_pool to settle before step_merge_findings\"\n        sub_steps:\n\n          step_sweep_native_batch:\n            description: \"Dispatch ALL native seats as a SINGLE PARALLEL BATCH (one parallel batch, NOT a sequential for_each)\"\n            skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n            dispatch_mode: parallel_batch\n            critical: |\n              NATIVE-PARALLEL REQUIREMENT: emit ALL native @deep-context Task dispatches in ONE batch\n              (a single set of concurrent Task calls), NOT one-at-a-time in a loop. Each native seat\n              gets the SAME current_focus and its own rendered prompt. Read-only analyzers.\n            batch:\n              for_each_native_seat: \"seat in native entries of config.fanout.executors\"\n              dispatch:\n                agent: deep-context\n                model: opus\n                read_only: true\n                context_source: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md\"\n                returns: \"structured findings (seat_output_schema)\"\n                host_writes: \"Host writes each seat's return to {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.json\"\n            wait_for_completion: true\n\n          step_sweep_cli_pool:\n            description: \"Dispatch ALL CLI seats as ONE-SHOT analysis seats over the SHARED focus, in parallel\"\n            skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n            dispatch_mode: one_shot_analysis_council\n            critical: |\n              ONE-SHOT-ANALYSIS REQUIREMENT (by-model shared scope): each CLI seat performs exactly ONE\n              read-only analysis pass over the SHARED current_focus this iteration — identical to a native\n              seat, just a different model lens. A CLI seat does NOT run its own loop. Use the council\n              parallel scaffold, NOT the autonomous-lineage runner, for the per-iteration sweep.\n            primary:\n              tool: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs#dispatchCouncilSeats\"\n              note: |\n                Orchestrate the CLI seats from the Node host via the council scaffold:\n                  dispatchCouncilSeats({ roundId, seats, dispatchSeat, context })\n                fans the seats out with Promise.all and aggregates per-seat results (fulfilled/rejected +\n                duration). roundId = \"iter-{current_iteration}\". seats = config.fanout.executors filtered to\n                kind != 'native', each carrying its rendered prompt path and the SHARED current_focus.\n              dispatch_seat: |\n                The injected per-seat dispatch function issues a SINGLE one-shot read-only CLI analysis\n                call — one `opencode run` / ` exec` / `claude -p` per seat — NOT a\n                loop. Build each invocation's per-kind flag shape by reusing\n                scripts/fanout-run.cjs#buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, sandbox, permission); the\n                difference is the PROMPT (one-shot analysis contract below, NOT buildLoopPrompt's\n                \"run phase_init/phase_main_loop/phase_synthesis\" text). The host then writes each seat's\n                returned findings JSON to {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.json.\n              one_shot_prompt_contract: |\n                Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true\n\n                Each seat's one-shot prompt carries the four-part lineage contract from\n                step_render_seat_prompts (gather-subject {scope} + SHARED current_focus + known-context +\n                seat_output_schema) and instructs the seat to return ONLY the structured-finding JSON for\n                this single pass. Apply the seat's promptFramework via sk-prompt-models\n                (MiMo→COSTAR, MiniMax/DeepSeek→TIDD-EC). Source the prompt body from the per-seat file\n                rendered at {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}/{seat.label}.md.\n            optional_autonomous_lineage_mode:\n              when: \"operator opt-in only (config.fanout.cliMode == 'autonomous-lineage'); NEVER the default per-iteration path\"\n              tool: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\"\n              command: |\n                node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n                  --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n                  --loop-type context \\\n                  --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_cli_json}' \\\n                  --base-artifact-dir {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\n              working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n              note: |\n                fanout-run.cjs spawns AUTONOMOUS FULL-LOOP lineages (buildLoopPrompt tells each subprocess\n                to run phase_init/phase_main_loop/phase_synthesis to convergence). That is the\n                research/review autonomous-lineage model — it is NOT by-model shared scope and must NOT be\n                used for the per-iteration parallel sweep. Reserve it for an explicit operator opt-in where\n                each CLI executor should run its OWN context loop end-to-end and the host merges the\n                lineage reports afterward (via scripts/fanout-merge.cjs), not per-iteration findings.\n            cli_contract:\n              - \"cli-opencode seats: dispatched with closed stdin (</dev/null) and NO top-level --agent (current opencode rejects --agent general); model id form per cli-opencode SKILL.md.\"","lineStart":360,"lineEnd":479,"totalLines":840,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782887165774,"end":1782887165781}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd73c08191962ba989317b6139"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2efa001TPDdrfGhNeQEEt","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165810,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fwTAwrzACgtM6uAnAE3Z9WAA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # DEEP COUNCIL: MULTI-TOPIC SESSION LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n2: role: Deep AI Council Session Manager\n3: purpose: Multi-topic council deliberation with session-wide findings registry and cross-topic priors\n4: action: Run deep-ai-council session orchestration from setup through synthesis and memory save\n5: operating_mode:\n6:   workflow: iterative_multi_topic_loop\n7:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n8:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n9:   approvals: none\n10:   tracking: council_session_state\n11:   validation: adjudicator_verdict_stability\n12: \n13: operating_principles:\n14:   core: \"Session -> topic -> round state with registry-backed cross-topic priors\"\n15:   approach: \"Run bounded topic loops, persist final verdicts, feed prior fingerprints into later topics\"\n16:   mandate: \"Command surface is live. Persist ai-council/** artifacts as source-of-truth and replay derived graph state through deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council.\"\n17: \n18: user_inputs:\n19:   deliberation_topic: \"[DELIBERATION_TOPIC] - Overall council topic or question set. REQUIRED.\"\n20:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Packet/spec folder path for ai-council artifacts. REQUIRED.\"\n21:   max_rounds_per_topic: \"[MAX_ROUNDS_PER_TOPIC] - Default: 3.\"\n22:   max_topics_per_session: \"[MAX_TOPICS_PER_SESSION] - Default: 5.\"\n23:   saturation_threshold: \"[SATURATION_THRESHOLD] - Default: 0.20.\"\n24:   executor:\n25:     mode: \"[in-cli|external-cli] - Default: in-cli.\"\n26:     cli: \"[active-runtime|cli-opencode|cli-claude-code|cli-opencode] - One CLI per round.\"\n27:     model: \"[MODEL] - Runtime-selected default unless provided.\"\n28:     reasoning: \"[REASONING_LEVEL] - Optional executor-specific setting.\"\n29: \n30: context_loading:\n31:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n32:   purpose: \"Load prior council context and memory hints for the deliberation topic\"\n33:   mcp_integration:\n34:     tool: memory_context\n35:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n36:     parameters: { input: \"{deliberation_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n37:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n38: \n39: skill_reference:\n40:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n41:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md\n42:   scripts:\n43:     orchestrate_session: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs\n44:     findings_registry: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/lib/findings-registry.cjs\n45:     replay_graph: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\n46:   runtime_primitives:\n47:     session_state: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs\n48:     round_state: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/round-state-jsonl.cjs\n49:     cost_guards: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/cost-guards.cjs\n50:     graph_upsert: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council\n51:     graph_status: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs --loop-type council\n52:     graph_convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --loop-type council\n53: \n54: state_paths:\n55:   packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council\"\n56:   lock_file: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/.deep-ai-council.lock\"\n57:   session_config: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/council-session.json\"\n58:   session_state_log: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/session-state.jsonl\"\n59:   findings_registry: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/deep-ai-council-findings-registry.json\"\n60:   topics_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics\"\n61:   topic_report_pattern: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics/{topic_id}/topic-report.md\"\n62:   council_report_pattern: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics/{topic_id}/council-report.md\"\n63:   session_report: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/session-report.md\"\n64:   prompt_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/prompts\"\n65: \n66: workflow:\n67:   phase_setup:\n68:     purpose: \"Resolve inputs, initialize state paths, and build the session config\"\n69:     steps:\n70:       step_preflight_contract:\n71:         action: \"Validate required bindings and workflow contract before writes\"\n72:         verify:\n73:           - required_values_present: [deliberation_topic, spec_folder, max_rounds_per_topic, max_topics_per_session, saturation_threshold, executor]\n74:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/\"\n75:           - command_surface_activation: \"LIVE via ai-council.md and deep_ai-council_*.yaml\"\n76:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding\"\n77:       step_create_directories:\n78:         action: \"Create packet-local ai-council directories\"\n79:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.topics_dir} {state_paths.prompt_dir}\"\n80:       step_acquire_lock:\n81:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before building the session config\"\n82:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n83:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-ai-council run already holds this packet.\"\n84:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n85:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n86:         on_halt:\n87:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n88:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n89:         on_cancel:\n90:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel before sentinel processing\"\n91:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n92:         on_workflow_exit:\n93:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n94:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n95:       step_create_config:\n96:         action: \"Create council-session.json\"\n97:         populate:\n98:           deliberationTopic: \"{deliberation_topic}\"\n99:           maxRoundsPerTopic: \"{max_rounds_per_topic}\"\n100:           maxTopicsPerSession: \"{max_topics_per_session}\"\n101:           saturationThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n102:           # Semantic: adjudicator-verdict Round-N -> Round-N+1 stability delta. Lower = more rounds / higher stability requirement.\n103:           convergenceThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n104:           executor: \"{executor}\"\n105:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n106:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n107:           status: \"initialized\"\n108: \n109:   phase_loop:\n110:     purpose: \"Run the F2 session orchestrator with F3 registry wiring\"\n111:     steps:\n112:       step_build_session_state:\n113:         action: \"Map deliberation_topic into session -> topic -> round state\"\n114:         outputs:\n115:           - session_state: \"Council session state object consumed by orchestrate-session.cjs\"\n116:           - executor_config: \"Executor config with seats, cost guards, dispatch/adjudication functions, resolved_route_header, and route_fields\"\n117:           - resolved_route_header: \"Resolved route: mode=ai-council; target_agent=@ai-council; execution=multi_topic_session_round; state_source=ai-council/session-state.jsonl; depth_aware=true; do_not_switch_mode=true\"\n118:           - route_fields: { mode: ai-council, target_agent: \"@ai-council\", execution: multi_topic_session_round, state_source: \"ai-council/session-state.jsonl\", depth_aware: true, do_not_switch_mode: true }\n119:       step_orchestrate_session:\n120:         action: \"Run bounded multi-topic council session\"\n121:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs --session-state {session_state_json} --executor-config {executor_config_json}\"\n122:         writes:\n123:           - \"{state_paths.session_state_log}\"\n124:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n125:           - \"{state_paths.topics_dir}/**\"\n126:         outputs:\n127:           - session_result: \"topics_completed, topic_results, skipped_topic_ids, stop_reason\"\n128:         post_dispatch_validate:\n129:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs#validateSessionStateHierarchy\"\n130:           assert_jsonl_record_type: round_completed\n131:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, topic_id, round_id, round_number, mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n132:           route_proof:\n133:             mode: council\n134:             target_agent: deep-ai-council\n135:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n136:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=council target_agent=deep-ai-council\"\n137:           failure_reasons:\n138:             - route_proof_missing\n139:             - route_proof_mismatch\n140: \n141:   phase_synthesis:\n142:     purpose: \"Compile per-topic and session-wide council reports\"\n143:     steps:\n144:       step_compile_topic_reports:\n145:         action: \"Compile each topic's council-report.md and topic-report.md from round artifacts\"\n146:         inputs:\n147:           - \"{state_paths.topics_dir}\"\n148:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n149:       step_compile_session_report:\n150:         action: \"Compile session-report.md from per-topic council reports and registry priors\"\n151:         writes:\n152:           - \"{state_paths.session_report}\"\n153:         include:\n154:           - completed_topics\n155:           - skipped_topics\n156:           - final_verdicts\n157:           - cross_topic_priors\n158:           - stop_reason\n159: \n160:   phase_save:\n161:     purpose: \"Route completion context into memory save\"\n162:     steps:\n163:       step_memory_save:\n164:         action: \"Invoke memory:save routing after synthesis\"\n165:         command_hint: \"/memory:save spec_folder={spec_folder} recent_action='deep-ai-council multi-topic session complete'\"\n166:         writes:\n167:           - \"{spec_folder}/description.json\"\n168:           - \"{spec_folder}/graph-metadata.json\"\n169:           - \"{spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md\"\n170:       step_release_lock:\n171:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after the session save has resolved\"\n172:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n173:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# DEEP COUNCIL: MULTI-TOPIC SESSION LOOP (AUTO MODE)\nrole: Deep AI Council Session Manager\npurpose: Multi-topic council deliberation with session-wide findings registry and cross-topic priors\naction: Run deep-ai-council session orchestration from setup through synthesis and memory save\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_multi_topic_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: council_session_state\n  validation: adjudicator_verdict_stability\n\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Session -> topic -> round state with registry-backed cross-topic priors\"\n  approach: \"Run bounded topic loops, persist final verdicts, feed prior fingerprints into later topics\"\n  mandate: \"Command surface is live. Persist ai-council/** artifacts as source-of-truth and replay derived graph state through deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council.\"\n\nuser_inputs:\n  deliberation_topic: \"[DELIBERATION_TOPIC] - Overall council topic or question set. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Packet/spec folder path for ai-council artifacts. REQUIRED.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml","text":"# DEEP COUNCIL: MULTI-TOPIC SESSION LOOP (AUTO MODE)\nrole: Deep AI Council Session Manager\npurpose: Multi-topic council deliberation with session-wide findings registry and cross-topic priors\naction: Run deep-ai-council session orchestration from setup through synthesis and memory save\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_multi_topic_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: council_session_state\n  validation: adjudicator_verdict_stability\n\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Session -> topic -> round state with registry-backed cross-topic priors\"\n  approach: \"Run bounded topic loops, persist final verdicts, feed prior fingerprints into later topics\"\n  mandate: \"Command surface is live. Persist ai-council/** artifacts as source-of-truth and replay derived graph state through deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council.\"\n\nuser_inputs:\n  deliberation_topic: \"[DELIBERATION_TOPIC] - Overall council topic or question set. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Packet/spec folder path for ai-council artifacts. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_rounds_per_topic: \"[MAX_ROUNDS_PER_TOPIC] - Default: 3.\"\n  max_topics_per_session: \"[MAX_TOPICS_PER_SESSION] - Default: 5.\"\n  saturation_threshold: \"[SATURATION_THRESHOLD] - Default: 0.20.\"\n  executor:\n    mode: \"[in-cli|external-cli] - Default: in-cli.\"\n    cli: \"[active-runtime|cli-opencode|cli-claude-code|cli-opencode] - One CLI per round.\"\n    model: \"[MODEL] - Runtime-selected default unless provided.\"\n    reasoning: \"[REASONING_LEVEL] - Optional executor-specific setting.\"\n\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior council context and memory hints for the deliberation topic\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{deliberation_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md\n  scripts:\n    orchestrate_session: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs\n    findings_registry: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/lib/findings-registry.cjs\n    replay_graph: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\n  runtime_primitives:\n    session_state: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs\n    round_state: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/round-state-jsonl.cjs\n    cost_guards: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/cost-guards.cjs\n    graph_upsert: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council\n    graph_status: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs --loop-type council\n    graph_convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --loop-type council\n\nstate_paths:\n  packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council\"\n  lock_file: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/.deep-ai-council.lock\"\n  session_config: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/council-session.json\"\n  session_state_log: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/session-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/deep-ai-council-findings-registry.json\"\n  topics_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics\"\n  topic_report_pattern: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics/{topic_id}/topic-report.md\"\n  council_report_pattern: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/topics/{topic_id}/council-report.md\"\n  session_report: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/session-report.md\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{spec_folder}/ai-council/prompts\"\n\nworkflow:\n  phase_setup:\n    purpose: \"Resolve inputs, initialize state paths, and build the session config\"\n    steps:\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required bindings and workflow contract before writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [deliberation_topic, spec_folder, max_rounds_per_topic, max_topics_per_session, saturation_threshold, executor]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/\"\n          - command_surface_activation: \"LIVE via ai-council.md and deep_ai-council_*.yaml\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding\"\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create packet-local ai-council directories\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.topics_dir} {state_paths.prompt_dir}\"\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before building the session config\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-ai-council run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create council-session.json\"\n        populate:\n          deliberationTopic: \"{deliberation_topic}\"\n          maxRoundsPerTopic: \"{max_rounds_per_topic}\"\n          maxTopicsPerSession: \"{max_topics_per_session}\"\n          saturationThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n          # Semantic: adjudicator-verdict Round-N -> Round-N+1 stability delta. Lower = more rounds / higher stability requirement.\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n          executor: \"{executor}\"\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: \"Run the F2 session orchestrator with F3 registry wiring\"\n    steps:\n      step_build_session_state:\n        action: \"Map deliberation_topic into session -> topic -> round state\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"Council session state object consumed by orchestrate-session.cjs\"\n          - executor_config: \"Executor config with seats, cost guards, dispatch/adjudication functions, resolved_route_header, and route_fields\"\n          - resolved_route_header: \"Resolved route: mode=ai-council; target_agent=@ai-council; execution=multi_topic_session_round; state_source=ai-council/session-state.jsonl; depth_aware=true; do_not_switch_mode=true\"\n          - route_fields: { mode: ai-council, target_agent: \"@ai-council\", execution: multi_topic_session_round, state_source: \"ai-council/session-state.jsonl\", depth_aware: true, do_not_switch_mode: true }\n      step_orchestrate_session:\n        action: \"Run bounded multi-topic council session\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs --session-state {session_state_json} --executor-config {executor_config_json}\"\n        writes:\n          - \"{state_paths.session_state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.topics_dir}/**\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_result: \"topics_completed, topic_results, skipped_topic_ids, stop_reason\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs#validateSessionStateHierarchy\"\n          assert_jsonl_record_type: round_completed\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, topic_id, round_id, round_number, mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: council\n            target_agent: deep-ai-council\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=council target_agent=deep-ai-council\"\n          failure_reasons:\n            - route_proof_missing\n            - route_proof_mismatch\n\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: \"Compile per-topic and session-wide council reports\"\n    steps:\n      step_compile_topic_reports:\n        action: \"Compile each topic's council-report.md and topic-report.md from round artifacts\"\n        inputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.topics_dir}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n      step_compile_session_report:\n        action: \"Compile session-report.md from per-topic council reports and registry priors\"\n        writes:\n          - \"{state_paths.session_report}\"\n        include:\n          - completed_topics\n          - skipped_topics\n          - final_verdicts\n          - cross_topic_priors\n          - stop_reason\n\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: \"Route completion context into memory save\"\n    steps:\n      step_memory_save:\n        action: \"Invoke memory:save routing after synthesis\"\n        command_hint: \"/memory:save spec_folder={spec_folder} recent_action='deep-ai-council multi-topic session complete'\"\n        writes:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/description.json\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/graph-metadata.json\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md\"\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after the session save has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":173,"totalLines":173,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782887165801,"end":1782887165809}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd73c881919e5be2148f42f0c2"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2f4f001QNzD1sObuLRwxI","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887165812,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CJedpr5P01rAbiePO77Znznm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ COMPONENT: Goal OpenCode Plugin (mk-goal)                              ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ PURPOSE: Persist session goals and inject passive goal steering.        ║\n5: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n6: 'use strict';\n7: \n8: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n9: // 1. IMPORTS\n10: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n11: \n12: import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n13: import { appendFile, mkdir, open, readFile, rename, unlink } from 'node:fs/promises';\n14: import { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\n15: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n16: \n17: import { tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin/tool';\n18: \n19: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: // 2. CONSTANTS\n21: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n22: \n23: const PLUGIN_ID = 'mk-goal';\n24: const DEFAULT_STATE_DIR = fileURLToPath(new URL('../skills/.goal-state/', import.meta.url));\n25: const DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS = 4000;\n26: const DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS = 4000;\n27: const DEFAULT_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS = 4800;\n28: const DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS = 280;\n29: const DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS = 1200;\n30: const DEFAULT_MAX_AUTO_TURNS = 8;\n31: const DEFAULT_CONTINUATION_COOLDOWN_MS = 1500;\n32: const DEFAULT_MAX_WALL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\n33: const DISABLED_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\n34: const AUTONOMY_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY';\n35: const DEBUG_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_DEBUG';\n36: const CONTINUATION_LOG_FILENAME = '.continuation.log';\n37: const GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME = '.goal-events.log';\n38: const PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_VERSION = 'sk-prompt-goal-v1';\n39: const PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_FRAMEWORK = 'CRAFT+TIDD-EC';\n40: const PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_METHODOLOGY = 'DEPTH';\n41: const PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_MODE = 'standard';\n42: const PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_PERSPECTIVES = [\n43:   'prompt_engineering',\n44:   'ai_interpretation',\n45:   'user_clarity',\n46:   'framework_fit',\n47:   'token_efficiency',\n48: ];\n49: const AUTONOMY_ACTIVE_MODES = new Set(['active', 'smoke']);\n50: const VALID_STATUSES = new Set([\n51:   'active',\n52:   'paused',\n53:   'blocked',\n54:   'usage_limited',\n55:   'budget_limited',\n56:   'complete',\n57: ]);\n58: const VALID_VERIFIER_VERDICTS = new Set(['met', 'not_met', 'blocked']);\n59: const EMPTY_INJECTION_PREVIEW = '';\n60: const GOAL_ACTIONS = ['set', 'show', 'clear', 'complete', 'pause'];\n61: const mutationQueues = new Map();\n62: \n63: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: // 3. ERRORS\n65: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: \n67: class GoalError extends Error {\n68:   constructor(code, message) {\n69:     super(message);\n70:     this.name = 'GoalError';\n71:     this.code = code;\n72:   }\n73: }\n74: \n75: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n76: // 4. PURE UTILITIES\n77: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n78: \n79: function normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback) {\n80:   return Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0 ? Math.trunc(value) : fallback;\n81: }\n82: \n83: function normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(value, fallback = DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS) {\n84:   return Math.min(DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS, normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback));\n85: }\n86: \n87: function normalizeOptions(rawOptions = {}) {\n88:   const envMaxObjectiveChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS);\n89:   const envMaxGoalPromptChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS);\n90:   const envMaxInjectionChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS);\n91:   const envMaxEvidenceChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS);\n92:   const options = rawOptions && typeof rawOptions === 'object' ? rawOptions : {};\n93: \n94:   return {\n95:     enabled: options.enabled !== false && process.env[DISABLED_ENV] !== '1',\n96:     stateDir: resolvePath(typeof options.stateDir === 'string' && options.stateDir.trim()\n97:       ? options.stateDir.trim()\n98:       : DEFAULT_STATE_DIR),\n99:     maxObjectiveChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n100:       options.maxObjectiveChars,\n101:       normalizePositiveInt(envMaxObjectiveChars, DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS),\n102:     ),\n103:     maxGoalPromptChars: normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(\n104:       options.maxGoalPromptChars,\n105:       normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(envMaxGoalPromptChars, DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS),\n106:     ),\n107:     maxInjectionChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n108:       options.maxInjectionChars,\n109:       normalizePositiveInt(envMaxInjectionChars, DEFAULT_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS),\n110:     ),\n111:     maxEvidenceChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n112:       options.maxEvidenceChars,\n113:       normalizePositiveInt(envMaxEvidenceChars, DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS),\n114:     ),\n115:     nowMs: Number.isFinite(options.nowMs) ? Math.trunc(options.nowMs) : null,\n116:     goalIdFactory: typeof options.goalIdFactory === 'function' ? options.goalIdFactory : null,\n117:     supervisorVerifier: typeof options.supervisorVerifier === 'function' ? options.supervisorVerifier : null,\n118:   };\n119: }\n120: \n121: function nowMs(options = {}) {\n122:   return Number.isFinite(options.nowMs) ? Math.trunc(options.nowMs) : Date.now();\n123: }\n124: \n125: function isoFromMs(value) {\n126:   return new Date(value).toISOString();\n127: }\n128: \n129: function stableStringify(value) {\n130:   if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return JSON.stringify(String(value));\n131:   if (Array.isArray(value)) return `[${value.map((entry) => stableStringify(entry)).join(',')}]`;\n132:   return `{${Object.keys(value).sort().map((key) => `${JSON.stringify(key)}:${stableStringify(value[key])}`).join(',')}}`;\n133: }\n134: \n135: function normalizeSessionID(value) {\n136:   if (value === null || value === undefined) return null;\n137:   const normalized = typeof value === 'object' ? stableStringify(value) : String(value);\n138:   const trimmed = normalized.trim();\n139:   return trimmed ? trimmed : null;\n140: }\n141: \n142: function requireSessionID(value) {\n143:   const sessionID = normalizeSessionID(value);\n144:   if (!sessionID) {\n145:     throw new GoalError('MISSING_SESSION_ID', 'Missing session id; refusing to read or write shared goal state');\n146:   }\n147:   return sessionID;\n148: }\n149: \n150: function sessionIdFromInput(input) {\n151:   if (!input || typeof input !== 'object') return null;\n152:   return normalizeSessionID(\n153:     input.sessionID\n154:       || input.sessionId\n155:       || input.session?.id\n156:       || input.properties?.sessionID\n157:       || input.properties?.info?.sessionID\n158:       || null,\n159:   );\n160: }\n161: \n162: function sessionIdFromContext(context) {\n163:   if (!context || typeof context !== 'object') return null;\n164:   return normalizeSessionID(context.sessionID || context.sessionId || context.session?.id || null);\n165: }\n166: \n167: function sessionKeyForSession(sessionID) {\n168:   return Buffer.from(requireSessionID(sessionID), 'utf8').toString('hex');\n169: }\n170: \n171: function clampText(value, maxChars) {\n172:   const text = String(value ?? '');\n173:   if (text.length <= maxChars) return text;\n174:   return `${text.slice(0, Math.max(1, maxChars - 3)).trimEnd()}...`;\n175: }\n176: \n177: function sanitizeInlineText(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS) {\n178:   const text = String(value ?? '')\n179:     .replace(/[\\u0000-\\u001f\\u007f]+/g, ' ')\n180:     .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n181:     .trim()\n182:     .replace(/\\[\\/?active_goal[^\\]]*\\]/gi, '[goal-marker-redacted]')\n183:     .replace(/`{3,}/g, '\\'\\'\\'')\n184:     .replace(/\\b(system|developer|assistant|tool|user)\\s*:/gi, '$1-role:')\n185:     .replace(/\\b(ignore|disregard)\\s+(all\\s+)?(previous|prior)\\s+(instructions?|messages?)\\b/gi, '[instruction-redacted]');\n186:   return clampText(text, maxChars);\n187: }\n188: \n189: function sanitizePromptText(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS) {\n190:   const text = String(value ?? '')\n191:     .replace(/\\r\\n?/g, '\\n')\n192:     .replace(/[\\u0000-\\u0008\\u000b\\u000c\\u000e-\\u001f\\u007f]+/g, ' ')\n193:     .replace(/\\[\\/?active_goal[^\\]]*\\]/gi, '[goal-marker-redacted]')\n194:     .replace(/`{3,}/g, '\\'\\'\\'')\n195:     .replace(/\\b(system|developer|assistant|tool|user)\\s*:/gi, '$1-role:')\n196:     .replace(/\\b(ignore|disregard)\\s+(all\\s+)?(previous|prior)\\s+(instructions?|messages?)\\b/gi, '[instruction-redacted]')\n197:     .split('\\n')\n198:     .map((line) => line.replace(/[ \\t]+/g, ' ').trim())\n199:     .join('\\n')\n200:     .replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n')\n201:     .trim();\n202:   return clampText(text, maxChars);\n203: }\n204: \n205: function redactEvidence(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS) {\n206:   const text = sanitizeInlineText(value, maxChars)\n207:     .replace(/\\b(sk-[A-Za-z0-9_-]{8,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n208:     .replace(/\\b(gh[pousr]_[A-Za-z0-9_]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n209:     .replace(/\\b(xox[baprs]-[A-Za-z0-9-]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n210:     .replace(/\\b(AKIA[0-9A-Z]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n211:     .replace(/\\b(api[_-]?key|token|password|secret)\\s*[:=]\\s*['\"]?[^'\"\\s,;]+/gi, '$1=[secret-redacted]');\n212:   return clampText(text, maxChars);\n213: }\n214: \n215: function scoreEnhancedGoalPrompt(goalPrompt) {\n216:   const prompt = String(goalPrompt || '');\n217:   const hasRole = /(^|\\n)Role:/i.test(prompt);\n218:   const hasObjective = /(^|\\n)Objective:/i.test(prompt);\n219:   const hasMethod = /(^|\\n)Method:/i.test(prompt);\n220:   const hasSuccess = /(^|\\n)Success Criteria:/i.test(prompt);\n221:   const hasStop = /(^|\\n)Stop Conditions:/i.test(prompt);\n222:   const hasNoPlaceholders = !/\\[[A-Z_ ]+\\]|TODO|TBD|placeholder/i.test(prompt);\n223:   const safeLength = prompt.length > 120 && prompt.length <= DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS;\n224: \n225:   const correctness = hasObjective && hasNoPlaceholders ? 9 : 7;\n226:   const logic = hasMethod && hasStop ? 9 : 7;\n227:   const expression = safeLength && hasNoPlaceholders ? 13 : 10;\n228:   const arrangement = [hasRole, hasObjective, hasMethod, hasSuccess, hasStop].filter(Boolean).length >= 5 ? 9 : 7;\n229:   const reusability = 4;\n230: \n231:   return {\n232:     total: correctness + logic + expression + arrangement + reusability,\n233:     breakdown: {\n234:       correctness,\n235:       logic,\n236:       expression,\n237:       arrangement,\n238:       reusability,\n239:     },\n240:   };\n241: }\n242: \n243: function goalFocusHints(objective) {\n244:   const text = String(objective || '').toLowerCase();\n245:   const hints = [];\n246:   if (/\\b(fix|bug|error|fail|failing|broken|regression|debug)\\b/.test(text)) {\n247:     hints.push('Find the root cause before changing code; verify the fix against the failing symptom.');\n248:   }\n249:   if (/\\b(implement|build|add|create|upgrade|refactor|change|modify|patch)\\b/.test(text)) {\n250:     hints.push('Make the smallest correct implementation that satisfies the requested behavior.');\n251:   }\n252:   if (/\\b(test|tests|verify|validation|lint|green|pass)\\b/.test(text)) {\n253:     hints.push('Run the relevant verification commands and report exact pass/fail evidence.');\n254:   }\n255:   if (/\\b(review|audit|inspect|analy[sz]e|research)\\b/.test(text)) {\n256:     hints.push('Ground conclusions in concrete files, outputs, or cited evidence.');\n257:   }\n258:   if (hints.length === 0) {\n259:     hints.push('Clarify the concrete completion condition from available context, then execute until it is met or blocked.');\n260:   }\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 1676. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: Goal OpenCode Plugin (mk-goal)                              ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Persist session goals and inject passive goal steering.        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { appendFile, mkdir, open, readFile, rename, unlink } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nimport { tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin/tool';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: Goal OpenCode Plugin (mk-goal)                              ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Persist session goals and inject passive goal steering.        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { appendFile, mkdir, open, readFile, rename, unlink } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nimport { tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin/tool';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst PLUGIN_ID = 'mk-goal';\nconst DEFAULT_STATE_DIR = fileURLToPath(new URL('../skills/.goal-state/', import.meta.url));\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS = 4000;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS = 4000;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS = 4800;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS = 280;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS = 1200;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_AUTO_TURNS = 8;\nconst DEFAULT_CONTINUATION_COOLDOWN_MS = 1500;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_WALL_MS = 30 * 60 * 1000;\nconst DISABLED_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\nconst AUTONOMY_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY';\nconst DEBUG_ENV = 'MK_GOAL_DEBUG';\nconst CONTINUATION_LOG_FILENAME = '.continuation.log';\nconst GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME = '.goal-events.log';\nconst PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_VERSION = 'sk-prompt-goal-v1';\nconst PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_FRAMEWORK = 'CRAFT+TIDD-EC';\nconst PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_METHODOLOGY = 'DEPTH';\nconst PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_MODE = 'standard';\nconst PROMPT_ENHANCEMENT_PERSPECTIVES = [\n  'prompt_engineering',\n  'ai_interpretation',\n  'user_clarity',\n  'framework_fit',\n  'token_efficiency',\n];\nconst AUTONOMY_ACTIVE_MODES = new Set(['active', 'smoke']);\nconst VALID_STATUSES = new Set([\n  'active',\n  'paused',\n  'blocked',\n  'usage_limited',\n  'budget_limited',\n  'complete',\n]);\nconst VALID_VERIFIER_VERDICTS = new Set(['met', 'not_met', 'blocked']);\nconst EMPTY_INJECTION_PREVIEW = '';\nconst GOAL_ACTIONS = ['set', 'show', 'clear', 'complete', 'pause'];\nconst mutationQueues = new Map();\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. ERRORS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nclass GoalError extends Error {\n  constructor(code, message) {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'GoalError';\n    this.code = code;\n  }\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. PURE UTILITIES\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback) {\n  return Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0 ? Math.trunc(value) : fallback;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(value, fallback = DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS) {\n  return Math.min(DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS, normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback));\n}\n\nfunction normalizeOptions(rawOptions = {}) {\n  const envMaxObjectiveChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS);\n  const envMaxGoalPromptChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS);\n  const envMaxInjectionChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS);\n  const envMaxEvidenceChars = Number(process.env.MK_GOAL_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS);\n  const options = rawOptions && typeof rawOptions === 'object' ? rawOptions : {};\n\n  return {\n    enabled: options.enabled !== false && process.env[DISABLED_ENV] !== '1',\n    stateDir: resolvePath(typeof options.stateDir === 'string' && options.stateDir.trim()\n      ? options.stateDir.trim()\n      : DEFAULT_STATE_DIR),\n    maxObjectiveChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n      options.maxObjectiveChars,\n      normalizePositiveInt(envMaxObjectiveChars, DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS),\n    ),\n    maxGoalPromptChars: normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(\n      options.maxGoalPromptChars,\n      normalizeMaxGoalPromptChars(envMaxGoalPromptChars, DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS),\n    ),\n    maxInjectionChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n      options.maxInjectionChars,\n      normalizePositiveInt(envMaxInjectionChars, DEFAULT_MAX_INJECTION_CHARS),\n    ),\n    maxEvidenceChars: normalizePositiveInt(\n      options.maxEvidenceChars,\n      normalizePositiveInt(envMaxEvidenceChars, DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS),\n    ),\n    nowMs: Number.isFinite(options.nowMs) ? Math.trunc(options.nowMs) : null,\n    goalIdFactory: typeof options.goalIdFactory === 'function' ? options.goalIdFactory : null,\n    supervisorVerifier: typeof options.supervisorVerifier === 'function' ? options.supervisorVerifier : null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction nowMs(options = {}) {\n  return Number.isFinite(options.nowMs) ? Math.trunc(options.nowMs) : Date.now();\n}\n\nfunction isoFromMs(value) {\n  return new Date(value).toISOString();\n}\n\nfunction stableStringify(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return JSON.stringify(String(value));\n  if (Array.isArray(value)) return `[${value.map((entry) => stableStringify(entry)).join(',')}]`;\n  return `{${Object.keys(value).sort().map((key) => `${JSON.stringify(key)}:${stableStringify(value[key])}`).join(',')}}`;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSessionID(value) {\n  if (value === null || value === undefined) return null;\n  const normalized = typeof value === 'object' ? stableStringify(value) : String(value);\n  const trimmed = normalized.trim();\n  return trimmed ? trimmed : null;\n}\n\nfunction requireSessionID(value) {\n  const sessionID = normalizeSessionID(value);\n  if (!sessionID) {\n    throw new GoalError('MISSING_SESSION_ID', 'Missing session id; refusing to read or write shared goal state');\n  }\n  return sessionID;\n}\n\nfunction sessionIdFromInput(input) {\n  if (!input || typeof input !== 'object') return null;\n  return normalizeSessionID(\n    input.sessionID\n      || input.sessionId\n      || input.session?.id\n      || input.properties?.sessionID\n      || input.properties?.info?.sessionID\n      || null,\n  );\n}\n\nfunction sessionIdFromContext(context) {\n  if (!context || typeof context !== 'object') return null;\n  return normalizeSessionID(context.sessionID || context.sessionId || context.session?.id || null);\n}\n\nfunction sessionKeyForSession(sessionID) {\n  return Buffer.from(requireSessionID(sessionID), 'utf8').toString('hex');\n}\n\nfunction clampText(value, maxChars) {\n  const text = String(value ?? '');\n  if (text.length <= maxChars) return text;\n  return `${text.slice(0, Math.max(1, maxChars - 3)).trimEnd()}...`;\n}\n\nfunction sanitizeInlineText(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_OBJECTIVE_CHARS) {\n  const text = String(value ?? '')\n    .replace(/[\\u0000-\\u001f\\u007f]+/g, ' ')\n    .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n    .trim()\n    .replace(/\\[\\/?active_goal[^\\]]*\\]/gi, '[goal-marker-redacted]')\n    .replace(/`{3,}/g, '\\'\\'\\'')\n    .replace(/\\b(system|developer|assistant|tool|user)\\s*:/gi, '$1-role:')\n    .replace(/\\b(ignore|disregard)\\s+(all\\s+)?(previous|prior)\\s+(instructions?|messages?)\\b/gi, '[instruction-redacted]');\n  return clampText(text, maxChars);\n}\n\nfunction sanitizePromptText(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS) {\n  const text = String(value ?? '')\n    .replace(/\\r\\n?/g, '\\n')\n    .replace(/[\\u0000-\\u0008\\u000b\\u000c\\u000e-\\u001f\\u007f]+/g, ' ')\n    .replace(/\\[\\/?active_goal[^\\]]*\\]/gi, '[goal-marker-redacted]')\n    .replace(/`{3,}/g, '\\'\\'\\'')\n    .replace(/\\b(system|developer|assistant|tool|user)\\s*:/gi, '$1-role:')\n    .replace(/\\b(ignore|disregard)\\s+(all\\s+)?(previous|prior)\\s+(instructions?|messages?)\\b/gi, '[instruction-redacted]')\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((line) => line.replace(/[ \\t]+/g, ' ').trim())\n    .join('\\n')\n    .replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n')\n    .trim();\n  return clampText(text, maxChars);\n}\n\nfunction redactEvidence(value, maxChars = DEFAULT_MAX_EVIDENCE_CHARS) {\n  const text = sanitizeInlineText(value, maxChars)\n    .replace(/\\b(sk-[A-Za-z0-9_-]{8,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n    .replace(/\\b(gh[pousr]_[A-Za-z0-9_]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n    .replace(/\\b(xox[baprs]-[A-Za-z0-9-]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n    .replace(/\\b(AKIA[0-9A-Z]{12,})\\b/g, '[secret-redacted]')\n    .replace(/\\b(api[_-]?key|token|password|secret)\\s*[:=]\\s*['\"]?[^'\"\\s,;]+/gi, '$1=[secret-redacted]');\n  return clampText(text, maxChars);\n}\n\nfunction scoreEnhancedGoalPrompt(goalPrompt) {\n  const prompt = String(goalPrompt || '');\n  const hasRole = /(^|\\n)Role:/i.test(prompt);\n  const hasObjective = /(^|\\n)Objective:/i.test(prompt);\n  const hasMethod = /(^|\\n)Method:/i.test(prompt);\n  const hasSuccess = /(^|\\n)Success Criteria:/i.test(prompt);\n  const hasStop = /(^|\\n)Stop Conditions:/i.test(prompt);\n  const hasNoPlaceholders = !/\\[[A-Z_ ]+\\]|TODO|TBD|placeholder/i.test(prompt);\n  const safeLength = prompt.length > 120 && prompt.length <= DEFAULT_MAX_GOAL_PROMPT_CHARS;\n\n  const correctness = hasObjective && hasNoPlaceholders ? 9 : 7;\n  const logic = hasMethod && hasStop ? 9 : 7;\n  const expression = safeLength && hasNoPlaceholders ? 13 : 10;\n  const arrangement = [hasRole, hasObjective, hasMethod, hasSuccess, hasStop].filter(Boolean).length >= 5 ? 9 : 7;\n  const reusability = 4;\n\n  return {\n    total: correctness + logic + expression + arrangement + reusability,\n    breakdown: {\n      correctness,\n      logic,\n      expression,\n      arrangement,\n      reusability,\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction goalFocusHints(objective) {\n  const text = String(objective || '').toLowerCase();\n  const hints = [];\n  if (/\\b(fix|bug|error|fail|failing|broken|regression|debug)\\b/.test(text)) {\n    hints.push('Find the root cause before changing code; verify the fix against the failing symptom.');\n  }\n  if (/\\b(implement|build|add|create|upgrade|refactor|change|modify|patch)\\b/.test(text)) {\n    hints.push('Make the smallest correct implementation that satisfies the requested behavior.');\n  }\n  if (/\\b(test|tests|verify|validation|lint|green|pass)\\b/.test(text)) {\n    hints.push('Run the relevant verification commands and report exact pass/fail evidence.');\n  }\n  if (/\\b(review|audit|inspect|analy[sz]e|research)\\b/.test(text)) {\n    hints.push('Ground conclusions in concrete files, outputs, or cited evidence.');\n  }\n  if (hints.length === 0) {\n    hints.push('Clarify the concrete completion condition from available context, then execute until it is met or blocked.');\n  }","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":1676,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","time":{"start":1782887165807,"end":1782887165811}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e8bae63d465c5c0016a44b2fd73d0819180864c36deab29a3"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b2f6a001lalcaACt4B6M8U","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5ae162001R35U72ACqi0pnN"}}
