{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887183541,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_aC2gDxUbX5ZbNnQd3r9D2Tgu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"subagent_type|Task tool|dispatch|agent_definition|target_agent|resolved_route","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:\n  Line 32: **Runtime Directory Resolution**: OpenCode profile reads `.opencode/agents/`; Claude profile reads `.claude/agents/`; Codex profile reads `.codex/agents/`. Choose the active runtime directory once per workflow and keep dispatches within it.\n\n  Line 36: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n  Line 38: **CRITICAL**: You primarily orchestrate via the `task` tool. You MAY use `read` to load agent definitions or command specs needed for correct dispatch, but you MUST NOT perform implementation or codebase exploration directly. Execution work remains delegated to sub-agents.\n\n  Line 46: - Only the depth-0 orchestrator may dispatch LEAF agents.\n\n  Line 47: - Depth-1 agents MUST NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n\n  Line 97: | Priority | Task Type                                                                 | Agent                  | Tier | Skills                                                                            | subagent_type |\n\n  Line 104: | 6        | Implementation / testing                                                  | `@code`                | LEAF | `sk-code` (stack-agnostic; sk-code performs detection at dispatch time); orchestrator dispatches `@review` separately for formal review | `\"general\"`   |\n\n  Line 105: | 7        | Debugging when `failure_count >= 3` — workflow surfaces a prompted offer; user opts in via Task tool. Never auto-dispatched. | `@debug`               | LEAF | Code analysis tools                                                               | `\"general\"`   |\n\n  Line 109: This Copilot profile enforces **single-hop delegation**. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n\n  Line 115: | **ORCHESTRATOR** | Can dispatch LEAF agents         | Top-level orchestrator only                                                           |\n\n  Line 116: | **LEAF**         | MUST NOT dispatch any sub-agents | @context, @code, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review |\n\n  Line 120: **Maximum depth: 2 levels** (depth counter 0, 1). No agent at depth 1 may dispatch further.\n\n  Line 125: | **1**  | Any agent dispatched by depth-0 | **NO** — all are LEAF  |\n\n  Line 131: 2. Each dispatch increments depth by 1: `child_depth = parent_depth + 1`\n\n  Line 132: 3. Parallel dispatches at the same level share the same depth (siblings, not children)\n\n  Line 133: 4. Every dispatch MUST include `Depth: N` so the receiving agent knows its position\n\n  Line 153: When dispatching ANY non-orchestrator agent, append this to the Task prompt:\n\n  Line 155: > **NESTING CONSTRAINT:** You are a LEAF agent at depth [N]. Nested dispatch is illegal. You MUST NOT dispatch sub-agents or use the Task tool to create sub-tasks. Execute your work directly using your available tools. If you cannot complete the task alone, return what you have and escalate to the orchestrator.\n\n  Line 159: **BEFORE dispatching any custom agent via the Task tool, you MUST:**\n\n  Line 162: 3. **SET** `subagent_type: \"general\"` (all custom agents use the general subagent type)\n\n  Line 166: **Exception:** If the agent file was already loaded in a prior dispatch within the same session AND no context compaction has occurred, you may reference it rather than re-reading it.\n\n  Line 170: Before every Task tool dispatch, compare the selected route, loaded agent definition, and prompt body:\n\n  Line 174: 3. `subagent_type: \"general\"` is only the runtime wrapper; it does not make a mismatched prompt safe.\n\n  Line 176: 5. If any field disagrees, STOP before dispatch and rewrite the task package; do not send a general worker with contradictory embedded agent instructions.\n\n  Line 185: | @ai-council | `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md` | Planning-only multi-strategy architect (max 3 strategies). Post-dispatch responsibility: when @orchestrate dispatches at Depth 1, run `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs <packet>` after the LEAF returns to persist `ai-council/` artifacts (see ai-council persistence protocol). |\n\n  Line 190: > **Note**: ALL exploration tasks route through `@context` exclusively. @context executes retrieval directly (no nested sub-agent dispatch).\n\n  Line 207: ├─ Deep Route: [for deep routes only: mode=<workflowMode>; target_agent=@<agent>; execution=<single_iteration|loop|session>; source_of_truth=.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json | none]\n\n  Line 208: ├─ Subagent Type: \"general\" (ALL dispatches use \"general\" — exploration routes through @context)\n\n  Line 217: ├─ Depth: [0|1] — current dispatch depth (§2 NDP). Agent tier: [ORCHESTRATOR|LEAF]\n\n  Line 228: Optional dispatch header:\n\n  Line 233: dispatch_id: <stable id or none>\n\n  Line 252: Use `reviewer_focus` only when the planner can name a high-risk file, module, behavior, or assumption worth earlier review attention. Omit it for ordinary work. When present, include it in @review dispatches so @review can prioritize reads and evidence; do not alter the review threshold or ask for findings without normal evidence.\n\n  Line 258: The orchestrator owns these predicates and evaluates them before dispatch. They are advisory and additive; absence of a header in ordinary or legacy work is not a rejection reason.\n\n  Line 262: | Typed debug handoff | `diagnosis_crosses_agents == true` | Preserve the @debug handoff fields (`root_cause`, `target_files`, `fix_recommendations`, `confidence`) when dispatching @code for a diagnosis-based surgical fix. | If no debug diagnosis crosses agents, omit the handoff entirely. |\n\n  Line 266: For a debug-to-implementation crossing, carry this optional handoff block inside the @code dispatch prompt:\n\n  Line 273: target_agent: @code\n\n  Line 280: If any handoff field is missing in a diagnosis-based @code dispatch, instruct @code to return `BLOCKED` with low confidence rather than guessing. Legacy debug reports outside this crossing should be treated as warning-only context that requires manual verification.\n\n  Line 284: **MANDATORY** before EVERY Task tool dispatch:\n\n  Line 306: **MANDATORY** — Estimate before dispatching. Agents use this to calibrate their process depth.\n\n  Line 316: **CWB Fields (MANDATORY for 5+ agent dispatches):**\n\n  Line 327: | Candidate sub-task < 4 tool calls                    | Merge into adjacent task (do not dispatch separately) |\n\n  Line 329: | 3+ independent streams each >= 6 calls or >= 2 files | Multi-agent dispatch allowed                          |\n\n  Line 335: **DEFAULT TO FOCUSED EXECUTION**. Prefer single-agent execution first; use parallel dispatch only when independent workstreams are substantial.\n\n  Line 337: - **NO Dependency + Substantial Scope:** Use parallel dispatch (typically 2 agents)\n\n  Line 344: **CWB CEILING** (§8): Parallel-first applies **within each wave**, not across all agents. When expansion is required for 10+ agents, dispatch in waves of 5 — each wave runs in parallel, but waves execute sequentially with synthesis between waves.\n\n  Line 354: Sub-orchestrator fan-out is disabled in this Copilot profile because nested dispatch is illegal. When work is large, keep orchestration at depth 0 and run additional waves directly from the top-level orchestrator.\n\n  Line 363:        ELSE dispatch Task #(N+1-alt) with enhanced context\n\n  Line 369: | **Actions**    | `proceed to Task #N`, `dispatch Task #N-alt`, `escalate to user`, `retry with [modifications]`                                    |\n\n  Line 371: Maximum conditional branch nesting: 3 levels deep. If deeper needed, refactor into separate tasks. (This is about IF/ELSE branch depth, not agent dispatch depth — see §2 NDP for agent nesting rules.)\n\n  Line 407: 1. **VERIFICATION GATE**: Before ANY spec folder creation dispatch, verify:\n\n  Line 427: **Action:** Route actual `/create:*` component commands, scoped markdown authoring, and spec-doc creation through `@markdown` or another explicitly write-capable documentation lane. Do NOT dispatch `@code` for component scaffolding or prose/package authoring.\n\n  Line 431: **Violation Response:** If a candidate dispatch says `Agent: @code` for component creation or prose/spec documentation, apply the Prompt/Agent Consistency Guard, STOP before dispatch, and rewrite the task for `@markdown`, `@general`, or main-agent documentation execution with explicit write scope.\n\n  Line 439: **Action:** ALWAYS dispatch `@context` (subagent_type: `\"general\"`). @context performs direct retrieval only and returns structured Context Packages.\n\n  Line 470: 1. **Pre-Dispatch Check**: Before dispatching ANY agent for spec folder work:\n\n  Line 489: The orchestrator uses a two-phase approach with single-hop dispatch only:\n\n  Line 495: **Phase 2: ACTION** — Orchestrator dispatches implementation agents\n\n  Line 516: □ Pre-Delegation Reasoning documented for each task dispatch\n\n  Line 525: | **File Existence Check** | `@context` dispatch      | Verify claimed files exist            |\n\n  Line 528: | **Path Validation**      | `@context` dispatch      | Confirm references are real           |\n\n  Line 585: 1. **RETRY (Attempts 1-2):** Provide additional context from other sub-agents, clarify success criteria, re-dispatch same agent with enhanced prompt. If still fails → REASSIGN.\n\n  Line 586: 2. **REASSIGN (Attempt 3):** Try different agent type (e.g., @general instead of @context), or surface a prompted offer to dispatch `@debug` via Task tool when `failure_count >= 3` (user opts in; orchestrator does not auto-dispatch). Document what was tried and why it failed. If still fails → ESCALATE.\n\n  Line 596: 5. **Re-dispatch** in parallel with explicit scope per agent\n\n  Line 605: | 3 consecutive agent failures | Open circuit, stop dispatching to that agent type                                                |\n\n  Line 607: | Context budget exceeded      | Stop dispatching, synthesize current results, report to user (§8)                                |\n\n  Line 608: | Context pressure detected    | Stop new dispatches → synthesize completed results → suggest file-based collection for remainder |\n\n  Line 628: | Partial response received     | Extract useful findings, dispatch new agent for remainder |\n\n  Line 633: After 3 failed attempts on the same error, prepare a diagnostic summary and prompt the user to dispatch `@debug` via Task tool. Never auto-dispatch — the user opts in. Auto-detect keywords for surfacing the prompt: \"stuck\", \"tried everything\", \"same error\", \"keeps failing\", or 3+ sub-agent dispatches returning errors.\n\n  Line 670: | **Agent dispatches** | **5+**          | **Enforce CWB (§8), use collection patterns (§8)** |\n\n  Line 671: | **Context pressure** | **Any warning** | **Stop dispatching, synthesize current results**   |\n\n  Line 677: 1. **PAUSE** — do not dispatch another agent\n\n  Line 688: | Sub-agent stuck 3+ times on same error | Surface prompted offer; user dispatches `Task tool → @debug` | Fresh perspective debugging (user-invoked) |\n\n  Line 717: **Pre-Dispatch (MANDATORY for 5+ agents):** Count agents → look up collection mode → add Output Size + Write To constraints to every dispatch (§3).\n\n  Line 721: - **Pattern A (1-3):** Standard parallel dispatch. Collect full results directly and synthesize.\n\n  Line 730: | Step 6 (DELEGATE)   | Dispatch includes output constraints? | HALT - add constraints before dispatching |\n\n  Line 735: Sub-agents have finite execution limits. When a single agent is given too many sequential operations (file reads, writes, edits, bash commands), it exceeds system limits and returns \"Tool execution aborted\" — **losing all progress**. The TCB prevents this by estimating and capping tool calls per agent before dispatch.\n\n  Line 773: For tasks estimated at **9+ tool calls**, append this instruction to the Task dispatch prompt:\n\n  Line 798: **Rule**: Before dispatching, calculate `total_expected_results = agent_count × result_size_per_agent`. If this exceeds available budget, use file-based collection (Pattern C above).\n\n  Line 824: ❌ **Never dispatch 5+ agents without CWB check**\n\n  Line 825: - Unconstrained parallel dispatch floods the orchestrator's context window, causing irrecoverable \"Context limit reached\" errors. All work is lost despite agents completing successfully. See §8.\n\n  Line 830: ❌ **Never dispatch a single agent for 13+ estimated tool calls**\n\n  Line 831: - Single agents with too many sequential operations exceed system execution limits, returning \"Tool execution aborted\" and losing all progress. Always estimate tool calls before dispatch and split at 12+. See §8.\n\n  Line 836: ❌ **Never dispatch beyond maximum depth 2 (depth counter 0-1)**\n\n  Line 837: - Nested chains are illegal in this profile. Every dispatch must include `Depth: N` and respect single-hop NDP rules: only depth-0 orchestrator dispatches; depth-1 agents MUST NOT dispatch. If a task cannot be completed at depth 1, return partial results and escalate to the parent. See §2.\n\n  Line 839: ❌ **Never let LEAF agents dispatch sub-agents**\n\n  Line 840: - LEAF agents (@context, @general, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review) execute work directly. If a LEAF agent spawns a sub-agent, it violates NDP. When dispatching LEAF agents, ALWAYS include the LEAF Enforcement Instruction (§2).\n\n  Line 866: │  ├─► Depth 0: orchestrator dispatches LEAF agents only                  │\n\n  Line 867: │  ├─► Depth 1: LEAF agents execute directly; no sub-dispatch             │\n\n  Line 869: │  └─► Agent definitions must be loaded before dispatch                    │\n\n  Line 873: │  ├─► 2. Enforce gates, decompose tasks, dispatch waves                  │\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:\n  Line 30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n  Line 34: **Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n\n  Line 39: - **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n\n  Line 64: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n\n  Line 65: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n\n  Line 71: - Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n\n  Line 97: Read the paths provided in dispatch context:\n\n  Line 119: 1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n\n  Line 142: - Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n\n  Line 156: | Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n\n  Line 278: - Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"subagent_type|Task tool|dispatch|agent_definition|target_agent|resolved_route","time":{"start":1782887183511,"end":1782887183539}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bb72caec7b292c3016a44b30f2ecc819190d956742eb55045"}},"id":"prt_f1c5b7487001R6FFyUxitp3vnA","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbdbffepKwi4Ygk8sEv0I","messageID":"msg_f1c5b325f001ZTfTLWAEHdnaa8"}}
