,\"newInfoRatio\":0.12,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Captured what remains unproven without actual external smoke execution.\",\"answeredQuestions\":[\"KQ1\",\"KQ9\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:49:00Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":27,\"iteration\":27,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Implementation ordering stress-test\",\"findingsCount\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.10,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed decisive smoke must precede heavy FIX-5 work, but route-unification can be planned in parallel.\",\"answeredQuestions\":[\"KQ4\",\"KQ9\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:50:00Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":28,\"iteration\":28,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"KQ coverage audit\",\"findingsCount\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.08,\"noveltyJustification\":\"No new major facts; verified all KQs have evidence-backed answers.\",\"answeredQuestions\":[\"KQ1\",\"KQ2\",\"KQ3\",\"KQ4\",\"KQ5\",\"KQ6\",\"KQ7\",\"KQ8\",\"KQ9\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:51:00Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":29,\"iteration\":29,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"Decision synthesis adversarial pass\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.06,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Low novelty but clarified that operator symptoms justify escalation planning, not immediate FIX-5 implementation.\",\"answeredQuestions\":[\"KQ9\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:52:00Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":30,\"iteration\":30,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final max-iteration synthesis inputs\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.04,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Max-iteration run completed; final pass consolidated recommendations and eliminated alternatives.\",\"answeredQuestions\":[\"KQ1\",\"KQ2\",\"KQ3\",\"KQ4\",\"KQ5\",\"KQ6\",\"KQ7\",\"KQ8\",\"KQ9\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:53:00Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt-fast-high-1782886969751-3481xi\",\"totalIterations\":30,\"answeredCount\":9,\"totalQuestions\":9,\"stopReason\":\"max_iterations\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T06:54:00Z\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-strategy.md\n+# Deep Research Strategy: GPT Behavioral Hardening Follow-Up\n+\n+## Research Topic\n+GPT behavioral hardening follow-up for packet 031: ai-council subagent-only, orchestrate hardening v2, sub-agent enforcement plugin, GPT-vs-Claude benchmark, and FIX-5 unpark decision.\n+\n+## Known Context\n+- `resource-map.md` was not present in the spec folder at init; skipping coverage gate.\n+- Parent packet says phase 005 is blocked/inconclusive because 0/4 command-owned smokes reached leaf dispatch, and phase 006 remains parked on inconclusive evidence, not proof of sufficiency [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/spec.md:76-78].\n+- Phase 007 requires >=30 iterations and KQ1-KQ9 evidence-backed answers [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/spec.md:98-113].\n+\n+## Key Questions\n+- KQ1 decisive external smoke; KQ2 symptom mechanism; KQ3 ai-council mode; KQ4 orchestrate v2; KQ5 plugin enforcement; KQ6 benchmark; KQ7 literal-pattern; KQ8 propagation; KQ9 FIX-5 unpark.\n+\n+## Answered Questions\n+- KQ1-KQ9 answered in `research.md` with file:line evidence.\n+\n+## What Worked\n+- Registry-bound route analysis from `deep.md` and `mode-registry.json`.\n+- Existing validator and YAML route-proof fields.\n+- Plugin hook evidence from local plugin entrypoints.\n+\n+## What Failed\n+- Treating nested OpenCode smokes as decisive; phase 005 shows they stop at self-invocation/general-agent gates.\n+- Converting council to subagent-only as a shortcut; `mode: all` preserves direct depth-0 council behavior.\n+\n+## Exhausted Approaches\n+- Re-derive original taxonomy: out of scope and prior evidence is already caveated.\n+- Immediate FIX-5 implementation: too high blast radius without external smoke/benchmark evidence.\n+\n+## Ruled-Out Directions\n+| Approach | Reason | Evidence |\n+|---|---|---|\n+| Accept phase 005 as pass | Command-owned smokes failed before leaf dispatch | `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/005-gpt-verification-smoke/implementation-summary.md:99-104` |\n+| Make ai-council subagent-only now | Direct depth-0 seat dispatch is documented behavior | `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md:53-58` |\n+| Plugin as hard identity | Available plugin hooks transform messages/system context, not Task dispatch identity | `.opencode/plugins/mk-code-graph.js:442-518` |\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+Synthesis complete. Recommended next phase is external-shell smoke plus benchmark harness, followed by route-unification and optional prompt-transform enforcement plugin.\n+\n+## Non-Goals\n+- No code implementation in this lineage.\n+- No writes outside the lineage artifact directory.\n+\n+## Stop Conditions\n+- Completed exactly 30 iterations under `max-iterations`; convergence before iteration 30 was treated as telemetry only.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+{\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\"KQ1\", \"KQ2\", \"KQ3\", \"KQ4\", \"KQ5\", \"KQ6\", \"KQ7\", \"KQ8\", \"KQ9\"],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    { \"id\": \"f-ext-smoke\", \"question\": \"KQ1\", \"summary\": \"External non-OpenCode shell smoke is the only clean PASS/FAIL path for phase 005's blocked gate.\" },\n+    { \"id\": \"f-orchestrate-v2\", \"question\": \"KQ4\", \"summary\": \"Smallest orchestrate hardening is to delegate deep routes to deep.md/mode-registry rather than duplicate inference rules.\" },\n+    { \"id\": \"f-plugin-guardrail\", \"question\": \"KQ5\", \"summary\": \"A plugin can inject/validate prompt route contracts but cannot provide hard runtime identity from current hook surfaces.\" },\n+    { \"id\": \"f-fix5-wait\", \"question\": \"KQ9\", \"summary\": \"Do not unpark FIX-5 immediately; trigger it on external route-proof failure or benchmark-confirmed persistent regression after route-unification.\" }\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    \"Treat phase 005 as accepted\",\n+    \"Convert ai-council to subagent-only immediately\",\n+    \"Claim plugin-level prompt transform equals host hard identity\",\n+    \"Implement FIX-5 before external smoke/benchmark evidence\"\n+  ]\n+}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+# Deep Research Dashboard: gpt-fast-high\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n+|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n+| 1 | Charter and prior evidence floor | 0.92 | 4 | complete |\n+| 2 | External-shell smoke design | 0.86 | 5 | complete |\n+| 3 | Real-world symptom classification | 0.82 | 5 | complete |\n+| 4 | ai-council mode conversion risk | 0.76 | 4 | complete |\n+| 5 | orchestrate hardening v2 minimum edit | 0.74 | 5 | complete |\n+| 6 | Plugin hook feasibility | 0.70 | 4 | complete |\n+| 7 | Benchmark metric schema | 0.68 | 6 | 